Mplus 1p Thin Regular (Mplus1p-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mplus 1p' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Mplus 1p Thin'.

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mplus1p-Light', Everything looks good.

Mplus 1p Light Regular (Mplus1p-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mplus 1p' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Mplus 1p Light'.

Pass

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mplus1p-Regular', Everything looks good.

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mplus1p-Medium', Everything looks good.

Mplus 1p Medium Regular (Mplus1p-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mplus 1p' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Mplus 1p Medium'.

Pass

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mplus1p-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Mplus 1p ExtraBold Regular (Mplus1p-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mplus 1p' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Mplus 1p ExtraBold'.

Pass

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mplus 1p' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Mplus 1p Black'.

Pass

Mplus 1p Black Regular (Mplus1p-Black.ttf)

name

NID 16 does not contain any of the following keywords: 'Book, Ultra, Normal'

Mplus 1p Bold Bold (Mplus1p-Bold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mplus1p-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Mplus 1p Bold Bold (Mplus1p-Bold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
'space' in NID 6 cause issues in fontbook for Mac.

NID 6 is 'Mplus1p-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Mplus 1p Bold Bold (Mplus1p-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mplus1p-Bold', Everything looks good.
